  <span id="freeText15734515605976554477" style="display:none">This is an amazing book. I read it nearly 20 years ago, and if I were sent to Radio 4's Desert Island this would be my choice of book. It took me six months to read (and I'm a fast reader!)- I had to keep dipping in and out, as it is such a rich and complex text. Part SF, part historical fiction, and with more than a touch of magical realism it is a book I will re-read at some point. In it Elizabeth Tudor is married off to Philip II of Spain, Aztec gods are brought to life, and cinema is invented in Renaissance Italy. It is an absorbing, speculative and beautifully written doorstep of a book.</span>
